                    <div class="h-8 bg-gray-200 rounded"></div>
                    <div class="h-8 bg-gray-200 rounded w-1/2"></div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mt-8 mb-4">Adding Your First Products</h3>
          
          <div class="bg-white rounded-lg border border-gray-200 p-6">
            <h4 class="text-lg font-medium mb-4">Step 3: Create Your Product Catalog</h4>
            <p class="mb-4">Before adding individual products, we recommend setting up your product categories:</p>
            
            <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-3 mb-6">
              <li>Go to Inventory → Categories</li>
              <li>Click "Add Category" and create categories relevant to your business</li>
              <li>Once categories are set up, go to Inventory → Products</li>
              <li>Click "Add Product" and fill in the product details:
                <ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-5 mt-2 space-y-2">
                  <li>Name and description</li>
                  <li>SKU (Stock Keeping Unit)</li>
                  <li>Category</li>
                  <li>Purchase and selling prices</li>
                  <li>Initial stock level</li>
                  <li>Reorder level (for low stock alerts)</li>
                </ul>
              </li>
              <li>Save the product</li>
            </ol>
            
            <div class="bg-blue-50 border-l-4 border-blue-500 p-4">
              <p class="text-blue-700 text-sm"><strong>Pro Tip:</strong> You can also bulk import products using a CSV file. Go to Inventory → Import and download the template.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
