        <div class="prose prose-blue max-w-none">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-6">API Reference</h2>
          
          <p class="mb-8">SupplyFlow offers a REST API for integrating with other business systems. This section provides an overview of the API capabilities and how to use them.</p>
          
          <div class="bg-gray-50 border-l-4 border-gray-500 p-4 mb-8">
            <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Note:</strong> API access is available on Standard and Premium subscription plans only.</p>
          </div>
          
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mt-8 mb-4">API Authentication</h3>
          
          <div class="bg-white rounded-lg border border-gray-200 p-6 mb-8">
            <h4 class="text-lg font-medium mb-4">Generating API Keys</h4>
            <p class="mb-4">To use the SupplyFlow API, you'll need to generate API credentials:</p>
            
            <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-3 mb-6">
              <li>Go to Settings → API</li>
              <li>Click "Generate New API Key"</li>
              <li>Enter a description for the key (e.g., "Accounting Integration")</li>
              <li>Select the permissions for this key:
                <ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-5 mt-2 space-y-2">
                  <li>Read-only</li>
                  <li>Read/Write</li>
                  <li>Full access</li>
                </ul>
              </li>
              <li>Click "Generate Key"</li>
              <li>Copy and securely store your API key and secret - the secret will only be shown once</li>
            </ol>
            
            <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-lg p-4 mb-6">
              <h5 class="font-medium mb-2">Authentication Example (HTTP Headers)</h5>
              <div class="bg-gray-800 text-white font-mono text-sm p-4 rounded">
                <pre>Authorization: Bearer your_api_key_here
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json</pre>
              </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="bg-yellow-50 border-l-4 border-yellow-400 p-4">
              <p class="text-yellow-700 text-sm"><strong>Security Warning:</strong> Treat your API credentials like passwords. Do not share them or include them in client-side code. Always use HTTPS for API requests.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mt-8 mb-4">Available Endpoints</h3>
          
          <div class="bg-white rounded-lg border border-gray-200 p-6 mb-8">
            <h4 class="text-lg font-medium mb-4">API Endpoints Overview</h4>
            <p class="mb-4">The SupplyFlow API includes the following main endpoint categories:</p>
            
            <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-6">
              <table class="min-w-full divide-y divide-gray-200">
                <thead class="bg-gray-50">
                  <tr>
                    <th scope="col" class="px-6 py-3 text-left text-xs font-medium text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wider">Endpoint Category</th>
                    <th scope="col" class="px-6 py-3 text-left text-xs font-medium text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wider">Description</th>
