      <!-- Troubleshooting Section -->
      <section id="troubleshooting" class="pt-8 pb-16 border-t border-gray-200">
        <div class="prose prose-blue max-w-none">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-6">Troubleshooting</h2>
          
          <p class="mb-8">This section provides solutions to common issues you might encounter while using SupplyFlow, along with tips for resolving them.</p>
          
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mt-8 mb-4">Common Issues and Solutions</h3>
          
          <div class="bg-white rounded-lg border border-gray-200 p-6 mb-8">
            <div class="space-y-6">
              <div>
                <h4 class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-800 mb-2">Connection Issues</h4>
                <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg border border-gray-200">
                  <div class="px-4 py-3 border-b border-gray-200 flex items-center bg-red-50">
                    <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-5 w-5 text-red-500 mr-2" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                      <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 8v4m0 4h.01M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z" />
                    </svg>
                    <span class="font-medium text-red-700">Problem: Can't access SupplyFlow or frequently disconnected</span>
                  </div>
                  <div class="p-4">
                    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">This is usually caused by internet connectivity issues or browser problems.</p>
                    <p class="font-medium mb-2 text-gray-800">Solutions:</p>
                    <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700">
                      <li>Check your internet connection and try accessing other websites</li>
                      <li>Clear your browser cache and cookies</li>
                      <li>Try using a different browser</li>
                      <li>Disable browser extensions that might be interfering</li>
                      <li>If using mobile data, move to an area with better reception</li>
                      <li>If the problem persists, contact your internet service provider</li>
                    </ol>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
              
              <div>
                <h4 class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-800 mb-2">Inventory Discrepancies</h4>
                <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg border border-gray-200">
                  <div class="px-4 py-3 border-b border-gray-200 flex items-center bg-yellow-50">
                    <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-5 w-5 text-yellow-500 mr-2" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                      <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 8v4m0 4h.01M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z" />
                    </svg>
                    <span class="font-medium text-yellow-700">Problem: Physical inventory doesn't match system records</span>
                  </div>
                  <div class="p-4">
                    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Discrepancies between physical inventory and system records can occur for various reasons, including sales not being recorded, theft, or data entry errors.</p>
                    <p class="font-medium mb-2 text-gray-800">Solutions:</p>
                    <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700">
                      <li>Check the Stock Movement History report to identify unexpected changes</li>
                      <li>Verify that all sales are being properly recorded</li>
                      <li>Ensure that all stock receipts have been entered correctly</li>
                      <li>Look for unusual adjustments or patterns that might indicate theft</li>
                      <li>Conduct a full inventory count and reconciliation</li>
                      <li>Use the "Adjust Stock" feature to correct discrepancies, with clear notes</li>
                      <li>Implement more regular stock counts for high-value or fast-moving items</li>
                    </ol>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
              
              <div>
                <h4 class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-800 mb-2">Sync Conflicts in Offline Mode</h4>
                <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg border border-gray-200">
                  <div class="px-4 py-3 border-b border-gray-200 flex items-center bg-yellow-50">
                    <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-5 w-5 text-yellow-500 mr-2" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                      <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 8v4m0 4h.01M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z" />
                    </svg>
                    <span class="font-medium text-yellow-700">Problem: Data conflicts when reconnecting after offline use</span>
                  </div>
                  <div class="p-4">
                    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">When multiple devices are used offline and then reconnected, data conflicts can occur if the same items were modified differently.</p>
                    <p class="font-medium mb-2 text-gray-800">Solutions:</p>
                    <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700">
                      <li>Assign specific products or categories to different staff members to avoid overlap</li>
                      <li>When resolving conflicts, carefully review both versions and choose the most accurate one</li>
                      <li>After resolving conflicts, perform a spot check on affected inventory items</li>
                      <li>Minimize offline usage when possible, especially for critical inventory operations</li>
                      <li>Establish clear procedures for offline operations and sync conflicts</li>
                      <li>Train staff on proper procedures for offline mode and synchronization</li>
                    </ol>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
              
              <div>
                <h4 class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-800 mb-2">Payment Integration Issues</h4>
                <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg border border-gray-200">
                  <div class="px-4 py-3 border-b border-gray-200 flex items-center bg-red-50">
                    <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-5 w-5 text-red-500 mr-2" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                      <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 8v4m0 4h.01M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z" />
                    </svg>
                    <span class="font-medium text-red-700">Problem: Mobile money payments not processing or confirming</span>
                  </div>
                  <div class="p-4">
                    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Issues with payment processing can be caused by API connectivity problems, incorrect credentials, or service outages.</p>
                    <p class="font-medium mb-2 text-gray-800">Solutions:</p>
                    <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700">
                      <li>Verify that your payment API credentials are correct in Settings → Payment Methods</li>
                      <li>Check that the callback URL is properly configured in your mobile money merchant account</li>
                      <li>Ensure that the mobile phone number is entered correctly, including the country code</li>
